1
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:31,416
[KAZUYA sighs]
You finally answered!

2
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:33,458
Victorique,
there's an emergency!

3
00:00:34,541 --> 00:00:35,541
I really need your help.

4
00:00:35,625 --> 00:00:36,708
[VICTORIQUE sneezes]

5
00:00:36,791 --> 00:00:39,166
[KAZUYA]
"Gyick"? Who's Gyick?

6
00:00:39,250 --> 00:00:41,291
Victorique, stop playing around!

7
00:00:41,375 --> 00:00:42,333
[gasps]

8
00:00:45,583 --> 00:00:47,625
[KAZUYA screams]

9
00:00:47,708 --> 00:00:48,875
[LUIGI gasps]

10
00:00:48,958 --> 00:00:50,791
12:51 pm.

11
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:59,083
[dial tone]

12
00:02:30,375 --> 00:02:31,750
[VICTORIQUE]
He hung up.

13
00:02:42,416 --> 00:02:44,625
What on earth's
going on around here?

14
00:02:51,375 --> 00:02:53,458
[KAZUYA groans]
Ow...

15
00:02:55,541 --> 00:02:57,083
[KAZUYA]
You!

16
00:02:57,166 --> 00:02:58,291
That's right.

17
00:02:58,375 --> 00:03:01,333
My name's... Anastasia.

18
00:03:01,416 --> 00:03:03,125
Are you from Russia?

19
00:03:04,333 --> 00:03:06,583
[ANASTASIA] I only
recently came to Saubreme.

20
00:03:06,666 --> 00:03:09,541
One day, I was looking at
dresses in the store window.

21
00:03:11,458 --> 00:03:14,416
A woman invited me in
to try on my favorites.

22
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:15,708
Then it happened.

23
00:03:23,583 --> 00:03:24,541
[ANASTASIA gasps]

24
00:03:26,333 --> 00:03:28,458
And... you've been
there ever since?

25
00:03:28,541 --> 00:03:30,083
Somewhere inside Jeantan?

26
00:03:30,166 --> 00:03:32,791
[ANASTASIA grunts]
There was a window in the room.

27
00:03:32,875 --> 00:03:34,791
I could see the palace from it.

28
00:03:35,958 --> 00:03:38,750
They even took the great
eagle with two heads.

29
00:03:38,833 --> 00:03:40,375
But I managed to slip away.

30
00:03:42,166 --> 00:03:44,541
[KAZUYA] That's why you
were inside the box.

31
00:03:44,625 --> 00:03:47,750
The devil! He's coming for me!

32
00:03:47,833 --> 00:03:49,041
Calm down!

33
00:03:50,250 --> 00:03:53,250
[ANASTASIA]
We're all... sacrifices.

34
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:54,291
[KAZUYA gasps]

35
00:03:57,500 --> 00:04:00,208
[AUCTIONEER]
We'll start at thirty thousand!

36
00:04:00,291 --> 00:04:01,625
Do I hear thirty-five?

37
00:04:01,708 --> 00:04:03,916
[ANASTASIA]
The words of the ritual.

38
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:06,000
They summon him!

39
00:04:06,083 --> 00:04:08,083
I can still hear them.

40
00:04:09,708 --> 00:04:11,250
We're the cursed chosen!

41
00:04:11,333 --> 00:04:12,750
Once he takes us...

42
00:04:12,833 --> 00:04:14,291
...we never come back.

43
00:04:14,375 --> 00:04:15,666
Help me.

44
00:04:15,750 --> 00:04:16,875
Please!

45
00:04:22,541 --> 00:04:25,583
[KAZUYA] Yet another ghost
story turns out to be true.

46
00:04:25,666 --> 00:04:27,833
I don't like this trend.

47
00:04:27,916 --> 00:04:30,041
There has to be a
way to prove it.

48
00:04:30,125 --> 00:04:31,625
Maybe someone local.

49
00:04:31,708 --> 00:04:34,708
Someone who'd be around
Jeantan frequently.

50
00:04:34,791 --> 00:04:35,750
[gasps]

51
00:04:37,166 --> 00:04:39,583
Go to the police and tell
them I sent you there.

52
00:04:39,666 --> 00:04:42,041
Ask for Inspector Blois and
tell him what happened.

53
00:04:42,125 --> 00:04:42,875
I can't.

54
00:04:42,958 --> 00:04:44,000
It's okay.

55
00:04:44,083 --> 00:04:46,250
I'll catch up to you
as soon as I can.

56
00:04:46,333 --> 00:04:47,916
We're going to
save your friends.

57
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,458
I promise.

58
00:04:51,875 --> 00:04:53,083
[LUIGI]
You buyin' or not?

59
00:04:53,166 --> 00:04:54,541
[MANAGER sighs]

60
00:04:54,625 --> 00:04:57,333
I'll give you three coins
for it, and that's generous.

61
00:04:57,416 --> 00:04:58,625
[LUIGI grunts]

62
00:04:58,708 --> 00:05:01,083
Ugh! It's robbery
and you know it.

63
00:05:01,166 --> 00:05:03,458
--[KAZUYA] Ah! There you are!
--[LUIGI gasps]

64
00:05:03,541 --> 00:05:05,083
Excuse me!

65
00:05:08,666 --> 00:05:10,416
Yeah? What do you want, kid?

66
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:11,083
Hold on.

67
00:05:11,166 --> 00:05:12,333
Isn't that mine?

68
00:05:12,416 --> 00:05:14,041
You dropped it,
so it was fair game.

69
00:05:14,125 --> 00:05:15,500
[KAZUYA]
I need to talk to you.

70
00:05:15,583 --> 00:05:16,541
[LUIGI gasps]

71
00:05:22,583 --> 00:05:24,375
[KAZUYA] When I dropped
the coins you counted them

72
00:05:24,458 --> 00:05:25,791
before they hit the ground.

73
00:05:25,875 --> 00:05:28,250
Then there was that thing
with the decorators.

74
00:05:28,333 --> 00:05:29,916
You have a seriously
impressive talent

75
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:32,375
for numbers and recollection.

76
00:05:32,458 --> 00:05:34,958
I thought, with a memory
like that, you might remember

77
00:05:35,041 --> 00:05:37,958
the people who went into
Jeantan and never came back out.

78
00:05:38,041 --> 00:05:40,083
--[LUIGI] Forget it...
--[KAZUYA gasps]

79
00:05:40,166 --> 00:05:42,625
[LUIGI] Don't you think
I would have reported it?

80
00:05:42,708 --> 00:05:45,708
I tried, a few times.

81
00:05:45,791 --> 00:05:47,083
I went to the police.

82
00:05:47,166 --> 00:05:48,916
Told them everything I'd seen.

83
00:05:50,166 --> 00:05:53,083
[LUIGI] To them, I'm just a
street rat, as good as a thief.

84
00:05:53,166 --> 00:05:55,208
No one would believe me.

85
00:05:55,291 --> 00:05:57,083
No one.

86
00:05:57,166 --> 00:06:00,583
[KAZUYA]
Well... I believe you.

87
00:06:00,666 --> 00:06:01,916
I know this girl.

88
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,875
She's a lot like you.

89
00:06:03,958 --> 00:06:06,916
Amazingly smart
and talented, also.

90
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,875
Whenever I'm around her...

91
00:06:09,916 --> 00:06:12,083
[KAZUYA] Well, I get
mocked by her, actually.

92
00:06:12,166 --> 00:06:13,416
[LUIGI]
Huh?

93
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:14,833
[KAZUYA]
It's true.

94
00:06:14,916 --> 00:06:17,125
Victorique's always
calling me an idiot.

95
00:06:17,208 --> 00:06:19,291
She deserves the
cold she caught.

96
00:06:19,375 --> 00:06:21,958
She's pushed me around,
made fun of me, and almost

97
00:06:22,041 --> 00:06:23,958
--never takes me seriously.
--[sighs]

98
00:06:24,041 --> 00:06:26,250
Sometimes, I wonder
if she really even

99
00:06:26,333 --> 00:06:27,750
thinks of me as a friend.

100
00:06:27,833 --> 00:06:30,416
Agh! Where are you going?

101
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:31,875
[LUIGI]
Where else, Soft Touch?

102
00:06:31,958 --> 00:06:33,083
To the police.

103
00:06:33,166 --> 00:06:35,375
I just have to testify, right?

104
00:06:35,458 --> 00:06:36,708
I got a fee though.

105
00:06:37,750 --> 00:06:39,750
Another one of those
coins should do.

106
00:06:42,208 --> 00:06:43,333
Sure!

107
00:06:50,250 --> 00:06:51,416
Cécile.

108
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:53,916
Bring me a copy of every
Saubreme newspaper

109
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,500
from the past week.

110
00:06:56,875 --> 00:06:58,000
On the double!

111
00:06:58,083 --> 00:06:59,416
[sneezes]

112
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:01,333
Now listen, Victorique.

113
00:07:01,416 --> 00:07:03,083
Just because you got
a shot doesn't mean--

114
00:07:03,166 --> 00:07:04,500
[VICTORIQUE]
You're still here?

115
00:07:04,583 --> 00:07:06,416
[gasps] Right.

116
00:07:08,666 --> 00:07:10,250
[door opens]

117
00:07:11,291 --> 00:07:14,333
[footsteps]

118
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:19,166
What's... that?

119
00:07:21,500 --> 00:07:22,958
[LUIGI]
A Phantasmagoria.

120
00:07:23,041 --> 00:07:25,166
You like this kind of thing?

121
00:07:25,250 --> 00:07:27,916
Phantasma-- What now?

122
00:07:29,916 --> 00:07:34,333
[KAZUYA] "The greatest magician
of the age, Brian Roscoe."

123
00:07:34,416 --> 00:07:36,458
I feel like I've heard
that name before.

124
00:07:36,541 --> 00:07:37,750
[thump]

125
00:07:45,250 --> 00:07:46,875
[gasps] A doll?

126
00:07:47,916 --> 00:07:49,625
An automaton!

127
00:07:52,875 --> 00:07:54,375
[CROWD MAN]
There he is!

128
00:07:54,458 --> 00:07:56,750
[CROWD WOMAN]
Roscoe the teleporter!

129
00:08:01,916 --> 00:08:02,875
[gasps]

130
00:08:04,708 --> 00:08:05,958
I know him!

131
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:09,833
Carry the lady carefully;
she's fragile.

132
00:08:11,583 --> 00:08:12,541
[MAN A]
Lady?

133
00:08:15,291 --> 00:08:16,791
[ROSCOE]
You heard me correctly.

134
00:08:16,875 --> 00:08:19,250
Be careful. She caught a cold
rather abruptly this morning.

135
00:08:19,333 --> 00:08:24,083
[CROWD laughs]

136
00:08:24,166 --> 00:08:25,000
[VOICE sneezes]

137
00:08:25,083 --> 00:08:27,041
--[BOTH gasp]
--[CROWD gasps]

138
00:08:29,541 --> 00:08:31,250
[ROSCOE]
Now, like I said.

139
00:08:31,333 --> 00:08:34,750
Make sure you're as gentle and
considerate as you can be.

140
00:08:40,041 --> 00:08:41,000
[KAZUYA]
Huh?

141
00:08:47,916 --> 00:08:48,791
Let's move on.

142
00:08:48,875 --> 00:08:50,541
I'm starting to get creeped out.

143
00:08:50,625 --> 00:08:51,833
[KAZUYA]
Sure.

144
00:08:56,625 --> 00:09:00,708
[LUIGI] Last winter,
February 12th at 3:05 pm.

145
00:09:00,791 --> 00:09:04,416
This spring, May 3rd, 7:12 pm.

146
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:05,625
She entered Jeantan.

147
00:09:05,708 --> 00:09:06,791
[COPS gasp]

148
00:09:06,875 --> 00:09:07,875
[LUIGI]
And that was it.

149
00:09:07,958 --> 00:09:09,458
She never came out again.

150
00:09:09,541 --> 00:09:12,041
Next. Last summer, August 30th.

151
00:09:12,125 --> 00:09:13,416
Haven't seen her since

152
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:14,833
--10:02 that morning.
--Every picture he's chosen

153
00:09:14,916 --> 00:09:17,458
is the subject of an unsolved
missing persons case.

154
00:09:17,541 --> 00:09:19,541
Furthermore, the
times he mentioned?

155
00:09:19,625 --> 00:09:22,208
They correspond with
when they disappeared.

156
00:09:22,291 --> 00:09:23,458
What now?

157
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:25,333
Well...

158
00:09:25,416 --> 00:09:26,541
[door opens]

159
00:09:28,375 --> 00:09:30,833
I just concluded my
interview with the girl.

160
00:09:30,916 --> 00:09:33,083
Something's definitely
wrong at Jeantan.

161
00:09:33,166 --> 00:09:35,333
[ALL gasp]

162
00:09:35,416 --> 00:09:37,750
[SIGNORE] She's the daughter
of a prosperous noble family

163
00:09:37,833 --> 00:09:41,958
that was driven out of Russia
during the Revolution of 1917.

164
00:09:42,041 --> 00:09:43,416
After losing her parents,

165
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:46,708
she used the few relatives
she had to come to Saubure.

166
00:09:47,750 --> 00:09:50,208
At least, that's the
story she's told me.

167
00:09:50,291 --> 00:09:51,833
I'm confirming it.

168
00:09:51,916 --> 00:09:54,791
So, for the moment, we wait.

169
00:09:54,875 --> 00:09:58,166
Either way, we can't move
without solid proof.

170
00:10:01,666 --> 00:10:02,791
Okay, Squirrel.

171
00:10:02,875 --> 00:10:04,708
Call it. We have no choice.

172
00:10:04,791 --> 00:10:06,375
[sighs]

173
00:10:06,458 --> 00:10:08,375
You mean Victorique, right?

174
00:10:08,458 --> 00:10:11,750
You know, instead of using me,
you could call her yourself.

175
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:12,833
No!

176
00:10:16,166 --> 00:10:18,000
[coughs]

177
00:10:18,083 --> 00:10:20,333
You don't understand anything.

178
00:10:20,416 --> 00:10:23,083
Why do you think I wear
this hairstyle to begin with?

179
00:10:23,166 --> 00:10:25,833
[KAZUYA]
Uh... because you like it?

180
00:10:27,583 --> 00:10:28,875
Once upon a time,

181
00:10:28,958 --> 00:10:32,333
I reluctantly chose to rely
on that thing's power.

182
00:10:32,416 --> 00:10:35,958
There was a case. I had to solve
it, no matter what the cost.

183
00:10:36,041 --> 00:10:38,375
And as the Wolf's payment...

184
00:10:38,458 --> 00:10:40,666
Victorique made you?

185
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:43,500
Listen, Kujo. This thing
that you have with her.

186
00:10:43,583 --> 00:10:44,958
It's like getting gobs of money

187
00:10:45,041 --> 00:10:47,291
from a high-interest
loan shark for free!

188
00:10:47,375 --> 00:10:50,750
It's enviable, yet
absolutely baffling.

189
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:01,041
[KAZUYA]
Victorique...

190
00:11:03,291 --> 00:11:04,291
All right then.

191
00:11:04,375 --> 00:11:06,541
I'll call her on one condition.

192
00:11:06,625 --> 00:11:09,166
Next time, don't
use me to ask her.

193
00:11:10,250 --> 00:11:12,333
Interesting...

194
00:11:12,416 --> 00:11:14,416
Yet exceedingly simple.

195
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:16,250
[sneeezes]

196
00:11:16,333 --> 00:11:17,375
[CÉCILE]
Victorique!

197
00:11:17,458 --> 00:11:19,750
Kujo's on the phone again!

198
00:11:22,375 --> 00:11:23,541
[CÉCILE humming]

199
00:11:23,625 --> 00:11:25,000
--[VICTORIQUE blows nose]
--[CÉCILE gasps]

200
00:11:25,083 --> 00:11:26,291
Hey!

201
00:11:30,125 --> 00:11:31,791
[KAZUYA]
Victorique? Hello?

202
00:11:31,875 --> 00:11:32,875
Can you hear me?

203
00:11:32,958 --> 00:11:34,416
I have something
important to ask you!

204
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:37,416
[sighs] Kujo.

205
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:39,583
Why must you always
disrupt my tranquility

206
00:11:39,666 --> 00:11:40,916
with trivial matters?

207
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,250
[KAZUYA stammers]

208
00:11:42,333 --> 00:11:44,083
You've gotten dragged
into another case, right?

209
00:11:44,166 --> 00:11:46,458
And now you need my
help to solve it.

210
00:11:46,541 --> 00:11:48,875
[KAZUYA]
Um... Well, yeah.

211
00:11:48,958 --> 00:11:51,041
Sorry for being such a bother.

212
00:11:51,125 --> 00:11:53,166
But I hope you
know I'm grateful.

213
00:11:53,250 --> 00:11:55,083
I couldn't do this without you.

214
00:12:00,208 --> 00:12:03,291
I've already assembled most of
the fragments of chaos for you.

215
00:12:03,375 --> 00:12:04,875
[KAZUYA]
Huh?! How?

216
00:12:04,958 --> 00:12:06,500
[VICTORIQUE]
Isn't it obvious?

217
00:12:06,583 --> 00:12:09,750
My wellspring of wisdom
gave me all that I needed.

218
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:12,625
Sadly, I'm still missing
some key pieces.

219
00:12:14,333 --> 00:12:16,125
Now tell me everything, Kujo.

220
00:12:16,208 --> 00:12:18,041
And please, make it brief.

221
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:25,166
[VICTORIQUE sneezes, blows nose]

222
00:12:25,250 --> 00:12:27,958
Good. Now, I'll reorganize them.

223
00:12:29,250 --> 00:12:30,875
But first, is there
a paperweight

224
00:12:30,958 --> 00:12:33,916
you could use nearby?
Glass, preferably.

225
00:12:35,250 --> 00:12:36,750
Yeah, what do we do with it?

226
00:12:36,833 --> 00:12:38,708
[VICTORIQUE]
Drop it on the floor, what else?

227
00:12:38,791 --> 00:12:40,250
Huh?

228
00:12:40,333 --> 00:12:41,833
[VICTORIQUE] Don't "huh" me,
just do what I'm telling you!

229
00:12:41,916 --> 00:12:44,125
--[VICTORIQUE sneezes]
--[KAZUYA gasps]

230
00:12:49,166 --> 00:12:50,250
It shattered.

231
00:12:50,333 --> 00:12:51,625
So?

232
00:12:51,708 --> 00:12:53,333
[VICTORIQUE] You dropped
the paperweight in Jeantan

233
00:12:53,416 --> 00:12:55,125
from roughly the same height.

234
00:12:55,208 --> 00:12:57,125
But it didn't break on impact.

235
00:12:57,208 --> 00:12:58,958
Why is that?

236
00:12:59,041 --> 00:13:00,208
[KAZUYA]
I don't know.

237
00:13:00,291 --> 00:13:01,666
[VICTORIQUE] Because the
Blue Rose you dropped

238
00:13:01,750 --> 00:13:04,041
wasn't made of
glass, but diamond.

239
00:13:04,125 --> 00:13:05,583
[KAZUYA gasps]

240
00:13:05,666 --> 00:13:07,875
[VICTORIQUE] Something like that
wouldn't break from a fall.

241
00:13:07,958 --> 00:13:10,458
Kujo, what you saw
wasn't a paperweight,

242
00:13:10,541 --> 00:13:12,958
but the genuine article.

243
00:13:13,041 --> 00:13:14,541
The real Blue Rose diamond,

244
00:13:14,625 --> 00:13:17,541
stolen from Saubure Palace
during the Great War.

245
00:13:19,666 --> 00:13:21,166
[VICTORIQUE]
And Jeantan itself,

246
00:13:21,250 --> 00:13:23,333
while seemingly innocent
from the outside,

247
00:13:23,416 --> 00:13:26,583
is probably trading in works
of art lost to history.

248
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:39,375
--[footsteps]
--[COPS chattering]

249
00:13:39,458 --> 00:13:41,250
[COP A]
Inspector, we found it!

250
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:56,833
[KAZUYA]
This is proof, Mr. Garnier.

251
00:13:56,916 --> 00:13:59,041
Admit it, you kept the
missing people in here!

252
00:13:59,125 --> 00:14:01,333
That's just a warehouse, my boy.

253
00:14:01,416 --> 00:14:03,916
Though, I'll admit it
should be used more often.

254
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:06,125
Liar! [yelps]

255
00:14:06,208 --> 00:14:09,541
This isn't proof, Kujo!
It's circumstantial at best.

256
00:14:09,625 --> 00:14:11,916
I'm sorry, but if he says
it's just a warehouse,

257
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:14,666
then there's nothing we can
do. It's as simple as that.

258
00:14:14,750 --> 00:14:16,166
[KAZUYA]
Let me go, Inspector!

259
00:14:16,250 --> 00:14:18,583
[BLOIS] No! Not until
you calm down, okay?

260
00:14:18,666 --> 00:14:20,541
[KAZUYA]
I won't! I'm not wrong!

261
00:14:20,625 --> 00:14:23,166
The kidnapped children
were kept here!

262
00:14:23,250 --> 00:14:25,625
[VICTORIQUE] Kujo, if
you're going to get justice

263
00:14:25,708 --> 00:14:27,125
for that girl and the others,

264
00:14:27,208 --> 00:14:28,750
--you need solid evidence.
--Save them! That's your job...

265
00:14:28,833 --> 00:14:30,916
[BLOIS]
Get ahold of yourself!

266
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:32,333
[VICTORIQUE]
Use Blue John.

267
00:14:32,416 --> 00:14:33,833
Wherever Anastasia was kept

268
00:14:33,916 --> 00:14:36,333
is where you'll find the
missing artwork and children.

269
00:14:36,416 --> 00:14:38,250
We know it has at
least one window.

270
00:14:38,333 --> 00:14:40,458
We can use it to locate
the hidden room.

271
00:14:42,250 --> 00:14:43,500
[sneezes]

272
00:14:43,583 --> 00:14:45,000
[VICTORIQUE] That's where
the Blue John comes in.

273
00:14:45,083 --> 00:14:47,541
While you and Grévil keep
Mr. Garnier distracted,

274
00:14:47,625 --> 00:14:50,375
the police will mark every
window in the building.

275
00:14:52,291 --> 00:14:55,166
[GARNIER] All that hard work
and hullabaloo for nothing.

276
00:14:55,250 --> 00:14:58,375
I hope you enjoyed wasting
my time, at least.

277
00:14:59,416 --> 00:15:00,208
[GARNIER chuckles]

278
00:15:00,291 --> 00:15:01,750
[BLOIS laughs]

279
00:15:01,833 --> 00:15:02,791
[GARNIER]
Huh?

280
00:15:04,125 --> 00:15:06,041
I'm not sure that I did.

281
00:15:08,375 --> 00:15:10,333
Tell me, Garnier.

282
00:15:10,416 --> 00:15:13,333
Have you ever heard
of Blue John?

283
00:15:13,416 --> 00:15:15,833
It's sometimes used by
fake spiritualists,

284
00:15:15,916 --> 00:15:18,250
who grind it up to
use as ectoplasm.

285
00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:19,833
The reason for this?

286
00:15:26,166 --> 00:15:27,375
[KAZUYA]
In the dark...

287
00:15:27,458 --> 00:15:29,000
It glows blue.

288
00:15:31,166 --> 00:15:34,083
[KAZUYA] Anastasia,
one of your many victims.

289
00:15:34,166 --> 00:15:35,958
She told us that she
could see the palace

290
00:15:36,041 --> 00:15:37,791
from the room
where she was kept.

291
00:15:38,916 --> 00:15:41,083
[KAZUYA] So we marked
every window in the store

292
00:15:41,166 --> 00:15:43,166
facing that direction.

293
00:15:43,250 --> 00:15:44,875
I have a feeling
your hidden room

294
00:15:44,958 --> 00:15:46,916
won't stay that way for long.

295
00:15:49,791 --> 00:15:51,000
It's over!

296
00:15:51,083 --> 00:15:52,500
Now, will you cooperate

297
00:15:52,583 --> 00:15:54,916
or do you have yet another
cheap trick you'd like to try?

298
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:55,750
[GARNIER growls]

299
00:15:55,833 --> 00:15:56,916
I see it!

300
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:59,500
The seventh window
on the fifth floor!

301
00:15:59,583 --> 00:16:00,541
You heard him!

302
00:16:00,625 --> 00:16:02,750
Get to the fifth
floor and find it!

303
00:16:11,250 --> 00:16:12,833
--[BLOIS gasps]
--No way!

304
00:16:12,916 --> 00:16:15,750
Don't just stand there!
Follow her example!

305
00:16:25,416 --> 00:16:27,958
Sorry, kid, this
floor is closed.

306
00:16:30,416 --> 00:16:32,458
Get going, I'll
handle things here.

307
00:16:32,541 --> 00:16:34,125
[KAZUYA]
Right. Thanks!

308
00:16:48,125 --> 00:16:49,708
There you are.

309
00:16:51,416 --> 00:16:56,291
[RICH FOLK chattering]

310
00:16:56,375 --> 00:16:57,166
[KAZUYA gasps]

311
00:16:57,250 --> 00:16:58,416
What the...?

312
00:17:15,833 --> 00:17:19,041
[AUCTIONEER] We'll start the
bidding at thirty thousand.

313
00:17:19,125 --> 00:17:20,791
I have thirty-five!

314
00:17:20,875 --> 00:17:22,625
Any more?

315
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:23,958
Thirty-seven here!

316
00:17:24,041 --> 00:17:25,333
Forty!

317
00:17:25,416 --> 00:17:27,333
Forty-two! Fifty!

318
00:17:27,416 --> 00:17:29,250
Fifty thousand!

319
00:17:29,333 --> 00:17:30,916
Any more?

320
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:32,041
Well?

321
00:17:32,125 --> 00:17:33,083
--Sixty thousand!
--[KAZUYA] It wasn't

322
00:17:33,166 --> 00:17:34,833
Thank you, sir!
---a demonic ritual.

323
00:17:34,916 --> 00:17:36,833
They were selling
the art and children

324
00:17:36,916 --> 00:17:38,875
off to the highest bidders.

325
00:17:38,958 --> 00:17:41,916
[RICH FOLK gasping]

326
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,208
We're the police!

327
00:17:43,291 --> 00:17:45,416
Everyone, stay right
where you are!

328
00:17:48,208 --> 00:17:55,166
[RICH FOLK screaming]

329
00:18:00,333 --> 00:18:01,708
[SIGNORE]
Take him away.

330
00:18:07,041 --> 00:18:09,041
[sighs]

331
00:18:15,416 --> 00:18:17,458
[KAZUYA]
The eagle with two heads.

332
00:18:17,541 --> 00:18:20,375
She was talking about
the Romanov family crest!

333
00:18:33,958 --> 00:18:36,625
It's the real thing, after all.

334
00:18:36,708 --> 00:18:40,375
Victorique, it played
out just like you said.

335
00:18:40,458 --> 00:18:42,083
No surprise there.

336
00:18:47,500 --> 00:18:49,708
[CÉCILE] "Inspector Blois
and local police apprehended

337
00:18:49,791 --> 00:18:51,333
Saubreme celebrity, Garnier,

338
00:18:51,416 --> 00:18:54,208
after damming evidence suggested
his involvement in a string of

339
00:18:54,291 --> 00:18:58,333
gang-related treasure thefts
during and after Great War.

340
00:18:58,416 --> 00:19:01,333
He then used the resulting
funds to purchase Jeantan,

341
00:19:01,416 --> 00:19:03,458
where he would auction
off stolen artwork."

342
00:19:03,541 --> 00:19:10,208
[yawns] The big city sure
is a scary place these days.

343
00:19:10,291 --> 00:19:12,291
[BLOIS] That old
woman you told me about.

344
00:19:12,375 --> 00:19:15,333
Apparently, her daughter
was kidnapped as well.

345
00:19:15,416 --> 00:19:16,666
[KAZUYA]
I see.

346
00:19:16,750 --> 00:19:18,750
[BLOIS] The Superintendent
General of the Police is

347
00:19:18,833 --> 00:19:22,041
personally searching for the
remaining missing children.

348
00:19:22,125 --> 00:19:24,125
I want to believe
he'll find them all.

349
00:19:24,208 --> 00:19:25,291
But you know...

350
00:19:28,208 --> 00:19:28,958
--[LUIGI laughs]
--[BOTH gasp]

351
00:19:29,041 --> 00:19:31,166
Is something... funny?

352
00:19:36,041 --> 00:19:37,083
Thank you.

353
00:19:37,166 --> 00:19:38,875
Everyone's safe because of you!

354
00:19:38,958 --> 00:19:40,291
Oh, I didn't do much.

355
00:19:40,375 --> 00:19:41,666
[giggles]

356
00:19:41,750 --> 00:19:43,625
[BLOIS] I got in touch with
her remaining relatives.

357
00:19:43,708 --> 00:19:46,083
They should be around
to pick her up shortly.

358
00:19:46,166 --> 00:19:47,666
Good work.

359
00:19:47,750 --> 00:19:49,958
[LUIGI]
Chinese!

360
00:19:50,041 --> 00:19:51,291
Who are--?

361
00:19:51,375 --> 00:19:53,458
[LUIGI] Wow, your memory's
worse than I thought.

362
00:19:53,541 --> 00:19:55,500
I testified for you.

363
00:19:55,583 --> 00:19:57,166
Now where's my coin?

364
00:19:57,250 --> 00:19:58,458
It's you!

365
00:19:58,541 --> 00:20:00,833
You look so different now!

366
00:20:00,916 --> 00:20:01,750
[LUIGI]
Nice, huh?

367
00:20:01,833 --> 00:20:03,791
I'm going to boarding school.

368
00:20:03,875 --> 00:20:05,333
She's decided to be my patron,

369
00:20:05,416 --> 00:20:07,416
and even gave me
these new clothes.

370
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:08,958
[JACQUELINE]
It's been awhile, Grévil.

371
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:11,750
Still wearing that
funny hairstyle, I see.

372
00:20:11,833 --> 00:20:13,833
Yes, but it's nowhere
near as funny looking

373
00:20:13,916 --> 00:20:15,916
as your face, dear Jacqueline.

374
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:17,333
[KAZUYA]
They seem close.

375
00:20:17,416 --> 00:20:19,625
I wonder where they
know each other from?

376
00:20:19,708 --> 00:20:20,958
[LUIGI]
Hey!

377
00:20:21,041 --> 00:20:22,000
I'm Luigi.

378
00:20:22,083 --> 00:20:22,750
You are?

379
00:20:22,833 --> 00:20:23,833
Right!

380
00:20:23,916 --> 00:20:26,500
Introductions completely
slipped my mind.

381
00:20:28,458 --> 00:20:30,833
Kazuya. Kazuya Kujo.

382
00:20:30,916 --> 00:20:32,750
What a weird name.

383
00:20:32,833 --> 00:20:34,000
Thanks a lot!

384
00:20:34,083 --> 00:20:35,541
Listen up.

385
00:20:35,625 --> 00:20:38,666
I'm the third son of a proud
imperial soldier, so show some--

386
00:20:38,750 --> 00:20:39,833
Come on!

387
00:20:39,916 --> 00:20:42,166
Drop the serious act, kid.
Have some fun!

388
00:20:42,250 --> 00:20:43,666
What a face!

389
00:20:45,875 --> 00:20:48,958
This is an ironic twist of
fate, isn't it, Inspector?

390
00:20:49,041 --> 00:20:52,000
The long lost Blue Rose
of the royal family...

391
00:20:52,083 --> 00:20:54,791
Recovered by the now famous
son of the Marquis de Blois--

392
00:20:54,875 --> 00:20:56,833
That's all in the past now, sir.

393
00:21:03,750 --> 00:21:05,541
Thanks, Kujo!

394
00:21:05,625 --> 00:21:07,708
See you around! Take care, now!

395
00:21:07,791 --> 00:21:10,041
Sure! Same to you!

396
00:21:19,833 --> 00:21:21,125
[KAZUYA]
Victorique...

397
00:21:21,208 --> 00:21:23,333
I wonder how you're doing.

398
00:21:23,416 --> 00:21:26,125
I hope you've gotten
over your cold, at least.

399
00:21:34,041 --> 00:21:35,500
[BLOIS]
Pathetic.

400
00:21:35,583 --> 00:21:38,583
You're nothing more than an
ignorant princess in a tower.

401
00:21:38,666 --> 00:21:40,291
That isn't true.

402
00:21:40,375 --> 00:21:43,250
[BLOIS] This hairstyle
means nothing to me.

403
00:21:43,333 --> 00:21:46,125
If you truly wanted
to make me despair,

404
00:21:46,208 --> 00:21:49,583
you should have made
your request far crueler.

405
00:21:49,666 --> 00:21:53,000
Then again...
You'd never think of it.

406
00:21:53,083 --> 00:21:54,833
--[VICTORIQUE sobs]
--[BLOIS] How could you?

407
00:21:54,916 --> 00:21:57,625
You've never loved anyone
in your miserable life.

408
00:21:57,708 --> 00:21:59,125
Not true...

409
00:21:59,208 --> 00:22:01,333
[BLOIS] You don't have the
power to bring someone misery.

410
00:22:01,416 --> 00:22:04,500
After all, Gray Wolves are
incapable of loving anyone!

411
00:22:04,583 --> 00:22:07,708
[VICTORIQUE]
You're wrong! It's not true!

412
00:22:07,791 --> 00:22:09,375
[VICTORIQUE]
It's not true at all!

413
00:22:09,458 --> 00:22:11,083
[BOTH gasp]

414
00:22:11,166 --> 00:22:12,416
[VICTORIQUE gasps]

415
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:17,250
Kujo... When'd you get here?

416
00:22:17,333 --> 00:22:18,625
[CÉCILE]
I swear!

417
00:22:18,708 --> 00:22:20,083
Sleeping in late again?

418
00:22:20,166 --> 00:22:21,541
That just won't do!

419
00:22:21,625 --> 00:22:24,083
So, are you feeling any better?

420
00:22:24,166 --> 00:22:26,916
You should, considering
you saved the day again.

421
00:22:28,125 --> 00:22:30,500
[VICTORIQUE clicks tongue]
Well, somebody had to.

422
00:22:30,583 --> 00:22:32,500
[KAZUYA] I brought you
a present from the city.

423
00:22:32,583 --> 00:22:33,333
Do you want it?

424
00:22:33,416 --> 00:22:34,541
Yes!

425
00:22:41,625 --> 00:22:45,000
[KAZUYA] Uh-- Is there something
you don't like about it?

426
00:22:48,458 --> 00:22:49,875
[VICTORIQUE gasps]

427
00:22:49,958 --> 00:22:53,125
Kujo, fetch my pipe, will you?

428
00:22:53,208 --> 00:22:54,375
[KAZUYA]
Sure!

429
00:22:59,500 --> 00:23:02,083
Yes. This will do nicely.

430
00:24:33,458 --> 00:24:36,000
[VICTORIQUE]
My brother has a dark secret.

431
00:24:36,083 --> 00:24:37,666
You see, Kujo.

432
00:24:37,750 --> 00:24:40,541
That drill...
is actually full of...

433
00:24:40,625 --> 00:24:42,208
...the sweetest candy!

434
00:24:42,291 --> 00:24:44,625
[KAZUYA]
Wha--?! You're kidding!

435
00:24:44,708 --> 00:24:46,125
What flavors?

